<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Adverb - English Grammar</title>
    <style>
        * {
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            box-sizing: border-box;
            font-family: 'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif;
        }

        body {
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #42275a, #734b6d);
            color: #333;
            min-height: 100vh;
            padding: 20px;
        }

        .container {
            max-width: 1000px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.95);
            border-radius: 20px;
            box-shadow: 0 10px 30px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
            overflow: hidden;
        }

        .header {
            background: linear-gradient(to right, #42275a, #734b6d);
            color: white;
            padding: 25px;
            text-align: center;
            position: relative;
        }

        .header h1 {
            font-size: 36px;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
            text-shadow: 2px 2px 4px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
        }

        .header p {
            font-size: 18px;
            opacity: 0.9;
        }

        .back-btn {
            position: absolute;
            top: 20px;
            left: 20px;
            background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2);
            color: white;
            border: none;
            padding: 8px 15px;
            border-radius: 20px;
            cursor: pointer;
            font-size: 14px;
            transition: all 0.3s;
        }

        .back-btn:hover {
            background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3);
            transform: translateX(-3px);
        }

        .content {
            padding: 30px;
        }

        .intro {
            text-align: center;
            margin-bottom: 30px;
            padding-bottom: 20px;
            border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;
        }

        .intro h2 {
            color: #42275a;
            margin-bottom: 15px;
            font-size: 28px;
        }

        .intro p {
            font-size: 18px;
            line-height: 1.6;
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: 0 auto;
        }

        .adverb-types {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr));
            gap: 25px;
            margin-bottom: 40px;
        }

        .type-card {
            background: white;
            border-radius: 15px;
            padding: 20px;
            box-shadow: 0 5px 15px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
            transition: transform 0.3s, box-shadow 0.3s;
            border-top: 5px solid #42275a;
        }

        .type-card:hover {
            transform: translateY(-5px);
            box-shadow: 0 8px 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15);
        }

        .type-card h3 {
            color: #42275a;
            margin-bottom: 15px;
            font-size: 22px;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
        }

        .type-card h3 span {
            background: #42275a;
            color: white;
            width: 30px;
            height: 30px;
            border-radius: 50%;
            display: inline-flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            margin-right: 10px;
            font-size: 16px;
        }

        .definition {
            margin-bottom: 15px;
            line-height: 1.6;
        }

        .example {
            background: #f8f9fa;
            padding: 12px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            border-left: 4px solid #734b6d;
            margin-bottom: 15px;
            font-style: italic;
        }

        .meitei-mayek {
            background: #fff8e1;
            padding: 12px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            border-left: 4px solid #fdbb2d;
        }

        .meitei-mayek h4 {
            color: #b21f1f;
            margin-bottom: 8px;
        }

        .epao-mayek {
            font-family: 'Nirmala UI', 'Noto Sans Meetei Mayek', sans-serif;
            font-size: 18px;
            line-height: 1.6;
        }

        .adverb-table {
            width: 100%;
            border-collapse: collapse;
            margin: 25px 0;
            box-shadow: 0 5px 15px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
            border-radius: 10px;
            overflow: hidden;
        }

        .adverb-table th {
            background: #42275a;
            color: white;
            padding: 15px;
            text-align: left;
        }

        .adverb-table td {
            padding: 12px 15px;
            border-bottom: 1px solid #e9ecef;
        }

        .adverb-table tr:nth-child(even) {
            background: #f8f9fa;
        }

        .test-section {
            background: linear-gradient(to right, #42275a, #734b6d);
            color: white;
            padding: 30px;
            border-radius: 15px;
            text-align: center;
            margin-top: 20px;
        }

        .test-section h2 {
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            font-size: 28px;
        }

        .options {
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            gap: 20px;
            flex-wrap: wrap;
        }

        .option-btn {
            padding: 12px 30px;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 30px;
            font-size: 18px;
            font-weight: bold;
            cursor: pointer;
            transition: all 0.3s;
            min-width: 150px;
        }

        .yes-btn {
            background: #4CAF50;
            color: white;
        }

        .yes-btn:hover {
            background: #45a049;
            transform: translateY(-3px);
        }

        .no-btn {
            background: #f44336;
            color: white;
        }

        .no-btn:hover {
            background: #da190b;
            transform: translateY(-3px);
        }

        .footer {
            text-align: center;
            padding: 20px;
            color: #666;
            font-size: 14px;
            margin-top: 30px;
            border-top: 1px solid #eee;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="header">
            <button class="back-btn" onclick="goBack()">← Back</button>
            <h1>Adverb</h1>
            <p>Describing how, when, where, and to what extent actions happen</p>
        </div>

        <div class="content">
            <div class="intro">
                <h2>What is an Adverb?</h2>
                <p>An adverb is a word that modifies a verb, adjective, or another adverb. It tells us how, when, where, or how often something happens.</p>
                <div class="meitei-mayek">
                    <h4>ꯑꯗꯚꯔꯕ ꯀꯔꯤꯅꯣ?</h4>
                    <div class="epao-mayek">
                        <p>ꯑꯗꯚꯔꯕ ꯑꯁꯤ ꯚꯔꯕꯗ ꯍꯧꯕꯥ ꯁꯔꯨꯛꯁꯤꯡꯗ ꯍꯧꯅꯥ ꯍꯧꯅꯕꯥ, ꯑꯃꯁꯤꯒꯤ ꯃꯇꯝ, ꯑꯍꯣꯡ ꯑꯃ ꯑꯇꯣꯡ ꯃꯥꯡꯕꯥ ꯁꯔꯨꯛꯁꯤꯡ ꯈꯪꯅꯩ꯫</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="adverb-types">
                <div class="type-card">
                    <h3><span>1</span> Adverb of Manner</h3>
                    <div class="definition">Tells how something happens or is done.</div>
                    <div class="example"><strong>Examples:</strong> quickly, slowly, neatly</div>
                    <div class="meitei-mayek"><h4>ꯍꯧꯅꯥ ꯑꯗꯚꯔꯕ</h4><div class="epao-mayek"><p>ꯈꯨꯗꯝ: ꯅꯩꯇꯨꯛꯅꯥ, ꯊꯧꯅꯥ</p></div></div>
                </div>

                <div class="type-card">
                    <h3><span>2</span> Adverb of Time</h3>
                    <div class="definition">Tells when an action happens.</div>
                    <div class="example"><strong>Examples:</strong> now, yesterday, soon</div>
                    <div class="meitei-mayek"><h4>ꯃꯇꯝꯗꯥ ꯑꯗꯚꯔꯕ</h4><div class="epao-mayek"><p>ꯈꯨꯗꯝ: ꯃꯇꯥꯡꯅꯥ, ꯑꯍꯣꯡꯗꯣꯛ</p></div></div>
                </div>

                <div class="type-card">
                    <h3><span>3</span> Adverb of Place</h3>
                    <div class="definition">Tells where an action happens.</div>
                    <div class="example"><strong>Examples:</strong> here, there, outside</div>
                    <div class="meitei-mayek"><h4>ꯃꯥꯍꯟꯗꯥ ꯑꯗꯚꯔꯕ</h4><div class="epao-mayek"><p>ꯈꯨꯗꯝ: ꯍꯧꯔꯤ, ꯊꯥꯔꯤ</p></div></div>
                </div>

                <div class="type-card">
                    <h3><span>4</span> Adverb of Frequency</h3>
                    <div class="definition">Tells how often an action happens.</div>
                    <div class="example"><strong>Examples:</strong> always, sometimes, never</div>
                    <div class="meitei-mayek"><h4>ꯃꯊꯧꯕꯥ ꯑꯗꯚꯔꯕ</h4><div class="epao-mayek"><p>ꯈꯨꯗꯝ: ꯍꯧꯗꯣꯛꯄꯤ, ꯃꯃꯤꯡꯁꯤꯡ</p></div></div>
                </div>

                <div class="type-card">
                    <h3><span>5</span> Adverb of Degree</h3>
                    <div class="definition">Tells the intensity or extent of an action.</div>
                    <div class="example"><strong>Examples:</strong> very, too, enough</div>
                    <div class="meitei-mayek"><h4>ꯃꯥꯡꯅꯥ ꯑꯗꯚꯔꯕ</h4><div class="epao-mayek"><p>ꯈꯨꯗꯝ: ꯃꯥꯡꯅꯥ, ꯋꯤꯡꯅꯥ</p></div></div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="intro">
                <h2>Adverb Functions in Sentences</h2>
                <p>Adverbs describe verbs, adjectives, or other adverbs by giving more detail about how, when, where, or to what degree something happens.</p>
                <div class="meitei-mayek">
                    <h4>ꯋꯥꯍꯩꯄꯔꯦꯡꯗꯥ ꯑꯗꯚꯔꯕꯒꯤ ꯊꯕꯛꯁꯤꯡ</h4>
                    <div class="epao-mayek"><p>ꯑꯗꯚꯔꯕ ꯑꯁꯤ ꯚꯔꯕ, ꯑꯦꯗꯖꯤꯛꯁꯤꯟ ꯑꯃ ꯑꯗꯚꯔꯕꯗ ꯍꯧꯕꯥ ꯁꯔꯨꯛꯁꯤꯡꯗ ꯑꯃꯁꯤꯒꯤ ꯃꯇꯝ ꯍꯧꯒꯠꯄꯥ ꯑꯃꯁꯤꯒꯤ ꯍꯧꯅꯥ ꯍꯧꯅꯕꯥ ꯇꯧꯏ꯫</p></div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <table class="adverb-table">
                <thead>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Function</th>
                        <th>Description</th>
                        <th>Example</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Modify Verb</td>
                        <td>Describes how an action happens</td>
                        <td>She runs <strong>quickly</strong>.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Modify Adjective</td>
                        <td>Intensifies or limits an adjective</td>
                        <td>He is <strong>very</strong> tall.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Modify Another Adverb</td>
                        <td>Changes the meaning of another adverb</td>
                        <td>He works <strong>too</strong> slowly.</td>
                    </tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>

            <div class="test-section">
                <h2>Want to Test Your Knowledge?</h2>
                <p>Take a short quiz to check how well you understand adverbs!</p>
                <div class="options">
                    <button class="yes-btn" onclick="location.href='adverbquiz.html'">Start Quiz</button>
                    <button class="no-btn" onclick="goBack()">Go Back</button>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="footer">
            © 2025 English Grammar by Thongam Jiten Singh | Designed for Learners
        </div>
    </div>

    <script>
        function goBack() {
            window.history.back();
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>
